{{> header}}

    <section id="wrapper">
      <header>
        <h1>Uncontext.</h1>
        <h2>Session 1&mdash;<span>{{#datasets}}{{name}}{{/datasets}}</span></h2>
      </header>

      <div class="intro">
        <span class="rule"></span>
        <p>Uncontext is an art project where any collaborator can access an unending stream of structured&mdash;but seemingly random&mdash;data. Use this data it to generate art, write poems, control robots, or anything else.</p>
        <span class="rule"></span>
      </div>

      <section class="section two-up">
        <div class="data-group">
          <h3>Data for this session</h3>
           <div class="data">
             <table>
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <td>a</td>
                  <td>b</td>
                  <td>c</td>
                  <td>d</td>
                  <td>e</td>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
              </tbody>
             </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="canvas-group">
          <h3>Example visualization</h3>
          <canvas id="homepage-canvas" width="400px" height="400px"></canvas>
          <div class="explanation">
            <ul>
              <li>When data.a is updated, a new line of circle is initiated, with that number of circles spaced along the x-axis.</li>
              <li>The size that the circles grows to is whatever data.b is at the time.</li>
              <li>If data.c === 0, the circles expand towards the right. If data.c === 1, then it&rsquo;s left.</li>
              <li>data.e.f / data.e.g determines the percentage along the y-axis the line runs along.</li>
              <li>Where's data.d? We don't need to use everything, silly.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h3>Just connect to <span class="small-mono">ws://literature.uncontext.com:80</span></h3>
        <div class="code">
<pre><code>// Look how freaking easy it is to get the data!

&lt;script&gt;
  socket_ = new WebSocket('ws://literature.uncontext.com:80');
  socket_.onmessage = function (data) {
    console.log(data);
  };
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

